    "year": 1908,
    "medium": "Oil and gold leaf on canvas",
    "dimensions": "180 cm × 180 cm",
    "location": "Österreichische Galerie Belvedere, Vienna",
    "description": "Klimt's most celebrated work depicts two lovers embracing on a flower-strewn cliff edge, their bodies dissolved into shimmering robes of gold. The painting's fusion of eroticism, Byzantine opulence, and modern abstraction has made it one of the most recognizable images in Western art.",
