    "dimensions": "138 cm × 138 cm",
    "location": "Neue Galerie, New York",
    "description": "Known as the 'Woman in Gold,' this portrait of Viennese socialite Adele Bloch-Bauer is Klimt's most lavish work. The subject's face and hands emerge from a shimmering field of gold leaf, silver, and intricate geometric and organic patterns drawn from Egyptian, Byzantine, and Japanese sources.",
