    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "84 cm × 42 cm",
    "location": "Österreichische Galerie Belvedere, Vienna",
    "description": "Klimt's provocative reimagining of the biblical heroine Judith presents her as a modern Viennese femme fatale, her expression one of ecstatic triumph as she cradles Holofernes' severed head. The gold leaf collar and decorative patterning create a striking contrast with the painting's sensual intensity.",
